This is a translation tool based on the goolge translation API. 
To run this tool :

1. Build it. 

ant compile

2. Run it :

The syntax is:

translate.sh -Dsource.language=sourceLangauge -Dsource.file=propertiesFile -Dtarget.language=targetLanguage -Dtarget.file=targetfile

Example:

translate.sh -Dsource.language=ENGLISH -Dsource.file=../../sipXconfig/neoconf/etc/sipxconference/conference.properties -Dtarget.language=FRENCH -Dtarget.file=conference_fr.properties

To translate a set of files proceed as follows:
1. Edit translateall.sh and change the target_language as needed.
2. Place the filepaths in sourcefiles
3. sh trnslateall.sh

The output will be placed in the same place as the files in the sourcefiles directory. For example 

../../sipXconfig/neoconf/etc/sipxconference/conference.properties

Gets translated to

../../sipXconfig/neoconf/etc/sipxconference/FRENCH-conference.properties
